:::summary
The Sun is the star at the center of our solar system — a blazing sphere of hot plasma that provides the light, heat, and energy upon which virtually all life on Earth depends. Created by God on the fourth day of creation (Genesis 1:14–19), the Sun has inspired awe, worship, and scientific inquiry across every civilization in history. Modern astrophysics reveals it to be a marvel of natural order, burning through nuclear fusion at its core and sustaining life across nearly 93 million miles of empty space.
:::

